WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.800
Hey there web explorers, we're looking at where to put JavaScript in your HTML.

00:05.800 --> 00:09.860
By the end of this video you'll know exactly where to place your scripts for maximum efficiency

00:09.860 --> 00:10.860
and flexibility.

00:10.860 --> 00:14.000
Let's get coding!

00:14.000 --> 00:19.240
First things first, JavaScript lives between script tags, that's like it's home.

00:19.240 --> 00:21.200
Let's start with an example.

00:21.200 --> 00:26.440
This simple script grabs an element with the ID of demo and changes its content.

00:26.440 --> 00:31.600
Bold examples might include type, equals text, slash javascript, but you don't need that

00:31.600 --> 00:32.600
anymore.

00:32.600 --> 00:38.000
It's like wearing socks with sandals, just don't.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.720
So where should you place your scripts?

00:39.720 --> 00:43.480
You can put them in the head, or body, or even both.

00:43.480 --> 00:46.760
Let's take a look at head.

00:46.760 --> 00:50.560
This works, but scripts in the head run before the page content loads.

00:50.560 --> 00:53.800
This might slow the rest of the page down.

00:53.800 --> 00:57.800
Let's try body.

00:57.800 --> 01:02.760
When the script's in the body, it runs as the page loads, making things snappier for

01:02.760 --> 01:05.920
users.

01:05.920 --> 01:08.440
Want to take things to the next level?

01:08.440 --> 01:12.240
External JavaScript is where it's at, it's like having a toolbox you can reuse on every

01:12.240 --> 01:14.400
page.

01:14.400 --> 01:21.040
Using external scripts keeps your code neat, reusable, and faster thanks to browser caching.

01:21.040 --> 01:25.960
You can reference external scripts in different ways, full URLs, relative paths, or no path

01:25.960 --> 01:27.720
at all.

01:27.720 --> 01:35.520
The choice depends on your setup, just remember, no script tags in your javascript files.

01:35.520 --> 01:40.120
So there you have it, scripts in the head, or body, inline, or external.

01:40.120 --> 01:43.720
It's all about what works for your project.

01:43.720 --> 01:48.160
Thanks for watching, like and subscribe to get notified about our latest videos.

01:48.160 --> 01:53.600
For more coding tips and tricks, keep it locked right here on w3schools.com.

01:53.600 --> 01:56.680
Don't forget to try out what you've learned in our interactive editor.

01:56.680 --> 01:57.480
Happy coding.

